[size=4][b]AutoPath[/b][/size]

Auto-advances your character on the map when only one path is available. No more clicking through obvious choices.

[size=3][b]Features[/b][/size]
[list]
[*][b]Auto-advance[/b] — when there's only one travelable node, your character moves there automatically after a short delay
[*][b]YOLO Mode[/b] — auto-advance through ALL paths, picking randomly at forks
[*][b]Configurable delay[/b] — adjust from 0.5s to 10s
[*][b]Multiplayer compatible[/b] — auto-votes for you in co-op; other players still need to agree
[*][b]Lightweight[/b] — single Harmony patch, zero performance impact
[/list]

[size=3][b]Installation[/b][/size]
[list=1]
[*]Download AutoPath.dll and AutoPath.json from the Files tab
[*]Create a folder: [font=Courier]Slay the Spire 2/mods/AutoPath/[/font]
[*]Place both files in that folder
[*]Launch STS2 → Settings → Mods → Enable AutoPath
[/list]

[size=3][b]Settings (requires ModConfig)[/b][/size]
Install [url=https://www.nexusmods.com/slaytheSpire2/mods/56]ModConfig[/url] to get an in-game settings panel:
[list]
[*][b]Selection Delay (sec)[/b] — slider from 0.5 to 10 seconds (default: 0.5)
[*][b]YOLO Mode[/b] — toggle to auto-advance even when multiple paths exist (picks randomly)
[/list]
Without ModConfig, AutoPath works with defaults (0.5s delay, YOLO off).

